<span id="Description"></span>
==Descrizione==

The [[Image:CAM_DressupLeadInOut.svg|24px]] [[CAM_DressupLeadInOut|CAM DressupLeadInOut]] command dresses up an existing path by adding lead-in and lead-out moves at the beginning and end of the toolpath.

==Usage==

# Select an existing path object.
# There are several ways to invoke the command:
#* Press the {{Button|[[Image:CAM_DressupLeadInOut.svg|16px]] [[CAM_DressupLeadInOut|Lead In/Out]]}} button.
#* Select the {{MenuCommand|CAM → Path Dressup → [[Image:CAM_DressupLeadInOut.svg|16px]] Lead In/Out}} option from the menu.
# Adjust the lead-in and lead-out settings in the task panel.
# Confirm the dressup.

==Options==

* '''Lead in''': Controls the entry move added before the main cutting path.
* '''Lead out''': Controls the exit move added after the main cutting path.
* '''Feed rate''': {{Version|26.3}} The corresponding lead-in and lead-out moves use the feed rates defined for these moves in the tool controller. By default these follow the horizontal feed rate.

==Limitations==

* This dressup modifies the start and end of an existing path.
* The exact result depends on the selected path and the chosen lead-in and lead-out settings.
* {{Version|26.3}} [[Image:CAM_DressupRampEntry.svg|16px]] [[CAM_DressupRampEntry|CAM DressupRampEntry]] can also be applied to a path that already has a Lead In/Out dressup.

